'''Alphie''' was an [[educational toy|educational]] [[robot]] toy popular in the 1980s<ref>{{cite web|last1=Coopee|first1=Todd|title=Alphie the Electronic Robot|url=https://toytales.ca/alphie-the-electronic-robot-from-playskool-1978/|website=Toy Tales}}</ref>. It featured a slot in the front for interchangeable cards which lined up with special soft-touch input function buttons built into the front of the toy. It ran on [[Battery (electricity)|batteries]] and came with different insert cards to help children learn [[Mathematics|math]], [[spelling]], matching skills, etc. The toy also played [[music]].<ref>{{cite web|title=computermuseum|url=http://www.computermuseum.li/Testpage/AlphieII-Playskook.htm|accessdate=November 8, 2013}}</ref>

The original Alphie was released in 1978.<ref>{{cite web|title=Alphie|url=http://www.robotsandcomputers.com/robots/alphie.htm|accessdate=November 8, 2013}}</ref>
Alphie II was released in 1983.

Reviews for the Alphie range from calling the Alphie "highly educational"<ref>{{cite web|title=Epinions Alphie Review|url=http://www.epinions.com/review/Hasbro_Alphie_The_Learning_Toy_Robot/content_599617670788?sb=1|accessdate=November 8, 2013}}</ref> to saying Alphie "scares [their] child".<ref>{{cite web|title=Amazon Alphie Review|url=https://www.amazon.com/Playskool-39350-Alphie/product-reviews/B003CRJU36/ref=cm_cr_dp_synop?ie=UTF8&showViewpoints=0&sortBy=bySubmissionDateDescending#RR6O2FS6O0B81|accessdate=November 8, 2013}}</ref>

