{{coord|40|43|15.7|N|74|00|16.7|W |display=title}} [[File:Canalroom.jpg|thumb|right|300px]] [[File:Canal Rm 285 WBwy jeh.jpg|thumb|250px|The exterior of the building which houses the Canal Room]] '''Canal Room''' was a music venue located at 285 [[West Broadway]] between [[Canal Street (Manhattan)|Canal Street]] and Lispenard Street in the [[Tribeca]] neighborhood of [[Manhattan]], [[New York City]]. The space was formerly known as "Shine". It underwent a $1 million renovation in 2003 by owner Marcus Linial, a former [[J Records]] "star".<ref>{{cite news |title=Fancy Feast |first=Trica |last=Romano |url=http://www.villagevoice.com/2003-08-26/nyc-life/fancy-feast/http |newspaper=The Village Voice |date=August 26, 2003 |accessdate=October 9, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Together Again: Analyze That! |first=George |last=Rush |first2=Joanna |last2=Molloy |first3=Suzanne |last3=Rozdeba |first4=Ben |last4=Widdicombe |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/archives/gossip/2003/08/24/2003-08-24_together_again__analyze_that_.html |newspaper=Daily News |location=New York |date=August 24, 2003 |accessdate=October 9, 2009}}</ref> The venue specialized in cover and tribute bands and accommodated approximately 450 people.<ref>{{cite news |title=Canal Room Brings in EAW KF730s |url=http://mixonline.com/news/audio_canal_room_brings/ |magazine=Mix |date=February 5, 2004 |accessdate=October 9, 2009}}</ref>
