{{Refimprove|date=March 2008}}
{{Infobox comic book title| <!--Wikipedia:WikiProject Comics--> title = The Goblin Chronicles | noimage = yes | caption = | schedule = | format = Miniseries | publisher = [[Ape Entertainment]] | date = March 19, 2008 - present | issues = 3 | main_char_team = | writers = Troy Dye & Tom Kelesides | artists = | pencillers = Collin Fogel | inkers = | colorists = Will Terrell | creative_team_month = | creative_team_year = | creators =
}}
'''''The Goblin Chronicles''''' is a three-issue [[comic book]] [[Limited series (comics)|mini-series]] created and written by Troy Dye and Tom Kelesides, penciled by Collin Fogel, colored by Will Terrell and lettered by David Hedgecock.
The Goblin Chronicles is a high-fantasy adventure story written for an “all ages” audience. Published by [[Ape Entertainment]], the first issue debuted in comic shops across North America on March 19, 2008.
The Goblin Chronicles is Ape Entertainment's first all-ages comic book published in the fantasy genre. Advance reviews were largely positive.<ref>[http://www.aintitcool.com/node/35449#11 Ain't It Cool News]</ref><ref>[http://brokenfrontier.com/reviews/details.php?id=1749 Broken Frontier]</ref><ref>[http://www.comicrelated.com/review/goblinchronicles1.html Comic Related]</ref><ref>[http://www.comicsintheclassroom.net/ooacats_meow2008_jan06.htm Comics in the Classroom]</ref>
'''''The Goblin Gadgeteer''''', a prequel story set in the world of The Goblin Chronicles, appeared in Ape Entertainment's 2007 [[Free Comic Book Day]] offering titled Ape's Entertainment's Comic Spectacular.<ref>[http://forum.newsarama.com/showthread.php?t=98901 ''Newsarama Announces Free Comic Book Titles for 2007'']</ref> The prequel story focused on one of the four main characters from the miniseries: Gorim the goblin.
Another prequel story, '''''A Tale of Two Shifters''''', appeared in the Fablewood Anthology,<ref>[http://www.fablewoodcomic.com/ Official Fablewood Anthology site]</ref><ref>[http://www.aintitcool.com/node/35607#10 Ain't It Cool News Review of the Fablewood Anthology]</ref> published by Ape Entertainment in February 2008. The story also featured one of the four main characters from the miniseries: Sprig the shape shifter.
